            <section class="prose mt-10" aria-label="Algebra reference">
              <h2>Core Algebra Formulas</h2>
              <h3>1. Linear equations</h3>
              <div class="formula-box">
                <code>ax + b = c</code> → <code>x = (c − b)/a</code>, with
                <code>a ≠ 0</code>.
              </div>

              <h3>2. Slope-intercept form</h3>
              <div class="formula-box">
                <code>y = mx + b</code> where <code>m</code> is the slope and
                <code>b</code> is the y-intercept.
              </div>

              <h3>3. Quadratic formula</h3>
              <div class="formula-box">
                <code>x = \frac{-b \pm \sqrt{b^2 - 4ac}}{2a}</code>
              </div>
              <p>If the discriminant <code>D = b² − 4ac</code> is:</p>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>positive</strong> → two real solutions</li>
                <li><strong>zero</strong> → one real (double) solution</li>
                <li><strong>negative</strong> → two complex solutions</li>
              </ul>

              <h3>4. Slope from points</h3>
              <div class="formula-box">
                <code>m = \frac{y_2 - y_1}{x_2 - x_1}</code>
              </div>
            </section>
